-- Citic Bank, China Merchants May Issue 70 Billion Yuan in Bonds
-- B y   W e n d y   M o c k
-- 2012-01-17T12:38:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/citic-bank-china-merchants-may-issue-70-billion-yuan-in-bonds.html
China Citic Bank Corp. (601998)  is proposing
to issue as much as 50 billion yuan in bonds, while  China
Merchants Bank Co. (60036)  received approval from regulators to issue as
much as 20 billion yuan of debt.  Citic plans to issue 20 billion yuan ($3.2 billion) of
subordinated bonds with a maturity of no less than five years
and 30 billion yuan of financial bonds with a maturity of no
more than five years, it said in a statement to the  Hong Kong 
Stock Exchange today.  It will use the proceeds of the subordinated bonds to
“replenish the supplementary capital of the bank” and to
increase its capital-adequacy ratio, the statement showed.
Proceeds from the financial bonds will be used “to support the
small and miniature enterprise loan business of the bank.”  China Merchants Bank received approvals for its  bond issue 
from the China Banking Regulatory Commission and the People’s
Bank of China, according to a separate statement to the
exchange. The proceeds will be used “for the extension of loans
to small and micro enterprises,” it said  To contact the reporter on this story:
